DagData - Class in hbl.jag.tri.lib
This class bundles together the class structures that will be used in the DagTri class as well as a number of utility routines to manipulate and summarize the data.
DagData(long[], long[], int) - Constructor for class hbl.jag.tri.lib.DagData
Constructor builds and initializes a DagData object
DagData(long[], long[], int, double[]) - Constructor for class hbl.jag.tri.lib.DagData
Alternate class constructor starts with right handed integer coordinate data arrays and also includes a optional double[] field of data defined on the same points (nominally a depth coordinate)
DagData(long[], long[], int, int[]) - Constructor for class hbl.jag.tri.lib.DagData
Alternate class constructor starts with right handed integer coordinate data arrays and also includes a bSeg array that indicates the fact that the array of verticies's begins with boundary segments listed in ccw order.
DagData(long[], long[], int, double[], int[]) - Constructor for class hbl.jag.tri.lib.DagData
Alternate class constructor starts with right handed integer coordinate data arrays with the inclusion of a third field associated with the same coordinate data (nominally depth) and then and also includes a bSeg array that indicates the fact that the array of verticies's begins with boundary segments listed in ccw order.
